    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "## Problem\n\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\nSource this code, notice nothing will be print at all. It seems `:sil!` also work for callback.. \n```lua\nlocal api, fn, uv = vim.api, vim.fn, vim.uv\nvim.cmd.cclose()\napi.nvim_create_autocmd(\"BufReadPost\", {\n\tpattern = \"quickfix\",\n\tgroup = api.nvim_create_augroup(\"test\", {}),\n\tcallback = function(ev)\n\t\t-- print(\"qf\", ev.buf)\n\t\tapi.nvim_buf_attach(ev.buf, true, {\n\t\t\ton_lines = function(...)\n\t\t\t\tif not _G.can_print then\n\t\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\t\tprint(\"this is never print\\n\")\n\t\t\t\tvim.schedule_wrap(print)(\"scheduled\\n\")\n\t\t\tend,\n\t\t})\n\tend,\n})\n\nvim.cmd.copen()\n\nvim.o.shortmess = vim.o.shortmess .. \"O\"\nlocal function loop()\n\t_G.can_print = true\n\tvim.defer_fn(function()\n\t\t-- vim._with({ silent = true }, function()\n\t\tassert(pcall(vim.cmd, [[sil! colder]]) or pcall(vim.cmd, [[sil! cnewer]]))\n\t\tprint(\"\\n\")\n\t\t-- end)\n\t\tloop()\n\tend, 1000)\nend\n\nfn.setqflist({ { text = uv.random(20):gsub(\"%c\", \"\") } })\nfn.setqflist({ { text = uv.random(20):gsub(\"%c\", \"\") } })\nloop(1)\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\nsilent shouldn't work in callback?\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-1917 gc53fb58c15` neovim/neovim@c53fb58c15\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.18.2-zen2-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
